A baby impling jar is the result of successfully catching a baby impling, while also having an empty impling jar. Baby impling jars are not that commonly looted because of the low value of the loot. Instead, the jar can be traded in singularly to Elnock Inquisitor for 3 empty impling jars. This allows the player to collect 3 more higher level implings for them to loot.

You can trade 3 of this jar, along with two young impling jars and one gourmet impling jar to Elnock for a vial of imp repellent.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening a baby impling jar gives 1,352 worth of loot, on average. This means opening baby impling jars marks an average profit of −1,753 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −175,267 to get an easy clue scroll, and −87,634 to get a beginner clue scroll from baby impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.

The following drop rates are provided by Jagex, unless otherwise specified.

Impling jar[edit | edit source]

An empty impling jar is returned when removing the loot, with a 10% chance of it breaking.[1]
